@node "Main" "Label Designer"
                         @{b} Label Designer V1.2
                        © 1995-1996 Markus Mader@{ub}

Sorry, this is no complete guide to Label Designer. But there are help
bubbles in the program. To show them, just place the mouse pointer over an
object and wait a few seconds. A detailed guide will only be released later
on, because I wanted to release a new version of Label Designer as soon as
possible as the version 1.0 had some problems with MUI 3.1.

Nevertheless I want to mention some important things:

  1. @{"Printer borders" link "DOC_PrinterBorders" 0}            IMPORTANT!
  2. @{"Preferences" link "DOC_Preferences" 0}                Pre-defined preferences
  3. @{"Registration" link "DOC_Registration" 0}               How to get the full version
  4. @{"The author" link "DOC_Author" 0}                 Contact the author
  5. @{"Licensing" link "DOC_Licencing" 0}
@endnode

@node "DOC_PrinterBorders" "Printer Borders"
@{b}@{u}Printer Borders@{ub}@{uu}

On the printer page in the preferences window you can edit the hardware
borders of your printer. These are the borders your printer is unable to
print on. If you want to print on single label papers, you have to enter
these borders unconditionally, because the page won't be printed correctly
otherwise. Set the borders to 0 if you use continuous label paper.

To find out the borders, proceed like this:

 1. Load the preferences file "PrinterBorders.prefs".
 2. Print a page of labels.
 3. Measure the borders and enter them in the string gadgets.
 4. Print another page of labels. If a second paper is drawn in after
    printing, increase the bottom border a bit. Repeat this procedure
    until no second paper is drawn in.
@endnode

@node "DOC_Preferences" "Preferences"
@{b}@{u}Preferences@{ub}@{uu}

In the prefs drawer there are some pre-defined settings for some paper
sorts. You can load them with the menu item "open" in the preferences
window. Then you only have to enter the @{"printer borders" link "DOC_PrinterBorders" 0}.
@endnode

@node "DOC_Registration" "Registration"
@{b}@{u}Registration@{ub}@{uu}

Label Designer is Shareware, this means that you have to register at the
author if you want to use the program without restrictions. The unregistered
version doesn't allow you to print own labels. You can just print a demo
label. The registered version doesn't have this restriction. To register
fill out the included registration form and send it together with DM 20.- or
an equivalent amount in another currency (cash or euro cheque) to:

             Markus Mader
             Angersiedlung 2
             96364 Marktrodach
             Germany
@endnode

@node "DOC_Author" "Author"
Please write me if you have found bugs or if you have problems with Label
Designer.

Besides I would be very nice if you send me your preferences for paper sorts
that are not supported by Label Designer yet. Please specify the producer,
the number, the size and the borders. Your printer model and the hardware
borders would also be interesting for me.

If you want to write a translation you can use the file LabelDesigner.ct in
the drawer "catalogs". Please send me your translation then, so that I can
include it in the Label Designer package.

My address:

  Markus Mader
  Angersiedlung 2
  96364 Marktrodach
  Germany
@endnode

